                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Jāmi‘ al-qavānīn</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa">جامع القوانین</title>
                            <note>
                                <p>Collected ornate letters (inshāʾ), also called <title>Inshā-yi
                                    Khalīfah</title>, by Khalīfah Shāh Muḥammad. Written while
                                    the author was studying at Qannauj, northern India (preface, f.
                                    2r), the work was completed in 1055/1645-6. </p>
                                <p>Comprises four faṣls and a khātimah. </p>
                                <p>Other contents: front inside cover and endpaper, descriptions by
                                    former owners (including: ‘M.S. Persan no. 8, Loix, préceptes et
                                    formules’), and bookplate of Le Ch. Ferrao de Castelbranco. </p>
                            </note>
